I see - the service is accessing `response.data.status` and `response.data.data.points`. The axios response wraps the API response in `.data`. So:
- `response.data` = the PointsBalanceApiResponse
- `response.data.data` = the nested `data` object
- `response.data.data.points` = the points value
- `response.data.status` = the status object

Wait, looking at the original card-place type:
```typescript
interface PointsBalanceApiResponse {
  data: {
    data: { points?: number };
    status: { returnCode?: number; codigoRetorno?: number; message?: string };
  };
}
```

So the type says `PointsBalanceApiResponse.data.data.points` and `PointsBalanceApiResponse.data.status`. But axios wraps the response in `.data`, so:
- `response.data` = `PointsBalanceApiResponse` 
- `response.data.data` would be `PointsBalanceApiResponse.data` (which contains `{data: {...}, status: {...}}`)
- So `response.data.data.points` would need another `.data` level

